if we use a proper â€œempireâ€ definition (centralized authority, multi-regional rule, bureaucracy, military expansion, multiethnic governance), Mesopotamia had more than just the â€œclassic fourâ€. Many smaller or earlier dynasties count as empires historically, even if popular sources skip them.

Hereâ€™s a more complete list of Mesopotamian empires, roughly in chronological order:

1. Akkadian Empire (c. 2334â€“2154â€¯BCE)

Founder: Sargon of Akkad

