Neo-Assyrian Empire (c. 911â€“609â€¯BCE) â€“ largest Mesopotamian empire, military dominance, Nineveh.

5. Mitanni / Hurrian Kingdom (c. 1500â€“1300â€¯BCE) (northern Mesopotamia & Syria)

Semimajor power controlling parts of northern Mesopotamia; sometimes counted as a Mesopotamian empire.

6. Kassite Babylonian Empire (c. 1595â€“1155â€¯BCE)

